<asp:Content ID="Content2" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder1" runat="server">
    <header class="aboutUs_header header">
        <div class="header_content">
            <h2 class="heading">ABOUT US</h2>
        </div>
    </header>
    <section>
        <div class="wrapper center">
            <h2 class="sub_heading">To be the Premier community cricket team in Canada.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="blocks">
            <div class="wrapper container block">
                <h2>OUR VALUES</h2>
                <p>
                    To provide to the community the opportunity, environment, and facilities to people of all ages and ability to play cricket. 
                    To promote the game of cricket in the Ontario area through our club values 
                    – Community, integrity, Respect, Team Work, Discipline and Enjoyment.
                </p>
                <br />
                <br />
                <div class="gallery_container gallery_container_small">
                    <div class="padding">
                        <h3>Community</h3>
                        <p>
                            Be an active and positive club within the community, welcome and open to people of all ages and abilities. 
                            Work to recognize Nepalese community in Canada through cricket.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="padding">
                        <h3>Integrity</h3>
                        <p>
                            Respect forms the basis of our sport. Respect the values and traditions of cricket, respect umpires and their decision’s, the opposition and the supporter. 
                            We value and respect the club and the peoples who help to run it.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="padding">
                        <h3>Leadership</h3>
                        <p>
                            We will, through our passion and commitment to cricket, lead the collective thoughts, ideas and needs of the cricket community and steward the direction of cricket in our province and community.
                            <br />
                            "Provide support and direction"
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="padding">
                        <h3>Team Work</h3>
                        <p>
                            Play selflessly for team and the club, on and off the field. 
                            We take pride in our team and rely on one another and understand that each player has a part to play.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="padding">
                        <h3>Discipline</h3>
                        <p>
                            Strong discipline underpins our sport; we obey the laws of game and we are always honest and fair. 
                            We play to win but not at all costs and recognize endeavor and achievement.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="padding">
                        <h3>Enjoyment</h3>
                        <p>
                            Enjoyment is the reason we play and support cricket. We use sport to adopt a healthy lifestyle and build skills. We safeguard our young players and help them to have fun while playing. 
                            We enjoy being part of a team and cricket family because it enhances confidence and self-esteem.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="block padding">
                <div class="wrapper">
                    <h2 class="center">HISTORY</h2>
                    <p class="padding">
                        Nepalese Canadian Cricket Club (NCCC) is community based cricket club which was established in 2017 by a group of youth with mission to promote cricket in youth and community. NCCC is registered as not for profit community club.
                        <br />
                        <br />
                        NCCC is first and only one registered Nepalese cricket club in Canada. NCCC made history participating 2018 Brampton Cricket League, representing Nepalese Community of Canada. NCCC also successfully organized first NCCC cup in 2018. Three Nepalese teams participated in the tournament; Team Everest was the winner of the tournament. NCCC generates revenue from sponsors, community members and club members.
                        <br />
                        <br />
                        NCCC uses the color of Nepal’s national flag in its jersey.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
